o sustain the\nobserved dust level is reasonable. We conclude that the hot exozodiacal dust\ndetected by near-infrared interferometry is unlikely to result from inwards\ngrains migration by Poynting-Robertson drag from a distant parent belt, but\ncould instead have an exocometary origin. [Abridged]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Mar 2019 17:03:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-05"}
